<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,1759,2037]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,313,1868,1892]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Remarks.</emphasis>
The synonymy was proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Werneburg" box="[696,901,1868,1892]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" refString="Werneburg, A. (1864) Beitrage zur Schmetterlingskunde. Part 1, Erfurt, Verlag von H. Neumann, 595 pp." type="book" year="1864">
Werneburg (
<number box="[835,894,1868,1892]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1864.0">1864</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and was repeated in Brown (
<number box="[1235,1294,1868,1892]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="2005.0">2005</number>
) and 
<bibRefCitation pageId="21" pageNumber="22" refString="Beccaloni, G., Scoble, M. J., Robinson, G. &amp; Pitkin, B. (Eds) (2005) The Global Lepidoptera Names Index (LepIndex). Natural History Museum London. Available from: http: // www. nhm. ac. uk / research-curation / research / projects / lepindex / (accessed: May 2011)." type="book chapter">
Beccaloni 
<emphasis box="[203,260,1904,1928]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[276,337,1903,1927]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. The name has never been used as senior synonym, and 
<taxonomicName box="[989,1158,1904,1928]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Isotrias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rectifasciana">
<emphasis box="[989,1158,1904,1928]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">I. rectifasciana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a well known species prevailing in the literature. According to the provisions of Article 23.9 (
<collectionCode box="[960,1027,1940,1964]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">ICZN</collectionCode>
<number box="[1035,1095,1940,1964]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1999.0">1999</number>
), we propose the conservation of Haworth’s name (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[384,597,1976,2000]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">nomen protectum</emphasis>
) and the suppression of the Fabrician name 
<taxonomicName box="[1099,1220,1976,2000]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Pyralis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trifasciana">
<emphasis box="[1099,1220,1976,2000]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">trifasciana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1237,1419,1975,2000]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">nomen oblitum</emphasis>
). Appendix 
<number box="[268,282,2012,2036]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="4.0">4</number>
lists 
<number box="[340,368,2012,2036]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="28.0">28</number>
references by more than ten different authors that have used 
<taxonomicName box="[1046,1214,2012,2036]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Isotrias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rectifasciana">
<emphasis box="[1046,1214,2012,2036]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">I. rectifasciana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the last 
<number box="[1335,1363,2012,2036]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="50.0">50</number>
years.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
